{"title_page": "Scott Dworkin", "text_new": "{{one source|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Scott Dworkin''' is an American podcast host and [[Democratic Party (U.S.)|Democratic]] fundraiser.\n\nIn 2009 he started Bulldog Finance Group, a consulting group that raised money to try from then to 2016 to elect a list of House candidates, with limited success.<ref name=\"mother-jones\" /> In 2016 he co-founded the [[Democratic Coalition Against Trump]] (then called \"Keep America Great\") [[super PAC]] with a goal of raising $20 million before the election; however, under 1% of that goal was raised.<ref name=\"mother-jones\" /> He has been criticized for a low percentage of spending by the super PAC being used on advertising.<ref name=\"mother-jones\" />\n\n== References ==\n<references>\n<ref name=\"mother-jones\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2019/07/scott-dworkin-resistance/ |title=The anti-Trump resistance has spawned a new crop of hucksters |first=Tim |last=Murphy |website=[[Mother Jones (magazine)|Mother Jones]] |date=July\u2013August 2019}}</ref>\n</references>\n\n\n{{us-politics-stub}}\n{{Uncategorized stub|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{single source|date=April 2020}}\n'''Scott Dworkin''' is an American podcast host and [[Democratic Party (U.S.)|Democratic]] fundraiser.\n\nIn 2009 he started Bulldog Finance Group, a consulting group that raised money to try from then to 2016 to elect a list of House candidates, with limited success.<ref name=\"mother-jones\" /> In 2016 he co-founded the [[Democratic Coalition Against Trump]] (then called \"Keep America Great\") [[super PAC]] with a goal of raising $20 million before the election; however, under 1% of that goal was raised.<ref name=\"mother-jones\" /> He has been criticized for a low percentage of spending by the super PAC being used on advertising.<ref name=\"mother-jones\" />\n\n== References ==\n<references>\n<ref name=\"mother-jones\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2019/07/scott-dworkin-resistance/ |title=The anti-Trump resistance has spawned a new crop of hucksters |first=Tim |last=Murphy |website=[[Mother Jones (magazine)|Mother Jones]] |date=July-August 2019}}</ref>\n</references>\n\n{{us-politics-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, addeduncategorisedtags", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scott_Dworkin"}
{"title_page": "FC Sputnik Rechitsa", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club\n  | clubname   = Sputnik Rechitsa\n  | image      = \n  | image_size = \n  | fullname   = Football Club Sputnik Rechitsa\n  | nickname   = \n  | shortname  = \n  | founded    = 2017\n  | dissolved  = \n  | ground     = [[Central Stadium (Rechitsa)|Central Stadium]], [[Rechitsa]]\n  | capacity   = 3,550\n  | chrtitle   = \n  | chairman   = \n  | mgrtitle   = Head coach\n  | manager    = [[Vyacheslav Levchuk]]\n  | league     = [[Belarusian First League]]\n  | season     = 2019\n  | position   = 6th\n<!-- kits tbd\n  | pattern_la1=|pattern_b1=_maroonhorizontal|pattern_ra1=|pattern_sh1=|leftarm1=FF0000|body1=FF0000|rightarm1=FF0000|shorts1=FF0000|socks1=FF0000|\n  | pattern_la2=|pattern_b2=_bluehorizontal|pattern_ra2=|pattern_sh2=|leftarm2=0A20E4|body2=0A20E4|rightarm2=0A20E4|shorts2=0A20E4|socks2=0A20E4|\n-->\n}}\n\n'''FC Sputnik Rechitsa''' is a [[Belarus]]ian [[Association football|football]] club based in [[Rechytsa]].\n\nThe club was founded in 2017 after a relocation of ''FC DYuSSh-DSK Gomel'' to Rechytsa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.football.by/news/98552.html|title=\u0420\u0435\u0447\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439 \"\u0421\u043f\u0443\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a\" \u0437\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442 \"\u041c\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0436\u043d\u0438\u043a\" \u0432\u043e \u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0439 \u043b\u0438\u0433\u0435 - \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 : Football.By : \u0411\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0438 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0444\u0443\u0442\u0431\u043e\u043b|website=www.football.by}}</ref>\nThe club finished third in the 2018 [[Belarusian Second League]] season and in early 2019, they were offered a promotion to the [[Belarusian First League|First League]], after a vacancy opened. Sputnik took the offer and will make its First League debut in 2019.\n\n==Current squad==\n''As of April 2020''\n\n{{Fs 